<div class="jumbotron">
  <h2>How many Computer Science questions can you answer?</h2>
  <p>The CS Challenge is an Open Source competitive educational game. Your answers (and speed) will be compared with other challengers.</p>
</div>

<div class="row login-features-container">
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-check"></span>Endure!</h3>
    <p>You might answer as many computer science questions you can until you miss one</p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-tower"></span>Compete!</h3>
    <p>The score will depend not only if you answer correctly, but also on how other people have answered it before!</p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-hourglass"></span>Hurry Up!</h3>
    <p>You have <strong>60 seconds</strong> to answer the question, also if you answer it fast enought you will get <strong>bonus points</strong>.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-time"></span>But rest</h3>
    <p>In between questions you might rest and take your time to understand what happened, you can even log out and continue with the next later on.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-signal"></span>Compare score</h3>
    <p>Once you are finished we will compare you proficiency with other computer scientists. Are you the very best who ever was?</p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-console"></span>Open source</h3>
    <p>All the code is available on github, The CS Challenge is powered with
      <strong><a href="http://emberjs.com" title="Javascript Framework Ember.js" target="_blank">Ember.js</a></strong> and
      <strong><a href="http://firebase.google.com" title="Firebase" target="_blank">Firebase</a></strong>.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">

  </div>
</div>

<div class="login-buttons text-center">
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary" {{action "signIn" "twitter"}}>Sign in with Twitter</button>
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary" {{action "signIn" "anonymous"}}>Anonymous sign in</button>
</div>
